John Lekashman wrote:
&gt;
&gt; Ok, is this a bug, or a feature?
&gt;


A &#39;feature&#39; that needs some tempering.

Heritrix is trying to get it all and will &#39;try&#39; likely looking text to 
see if is possibly a link.   Often this makes for 404s but, at least 
from our perspective as archivists, a couple of 404s are OK if our 
speculation on occasion finds a link-gem.

I haven&#39;t done the mental-decoding to figure how Heritrix arrived at 
http://www.igsoc.org/symposia/www.igsoc.org 
&lt;http://www.igsoc.org/symposia/www.igsoc.org&gt;, perhaps one of the other 
lads have it at their fingertips, but here&#39;s where you&#39;d start if you 
wanted to have a go yourself: 
http://crawler.archive.org/xref/org/archive/crawler/extractor/ExtractorHTML.html

While in there, check out this attribute: overly-eager-link-detection. 
It would seem to prevent speculations that build on HTML values and 
avoid conjuring URLs such as the one you ask below about.

Yours,
St.Ack





